# 2. バンドとは違う音

Miku: <Wow, so this is Vivid Street.>
Miku: <It's an interesting place, huh. So full of singers and music.>
Shiho: Yeah. There are a lot of musicians active in this area.
Shiho: Even Shiraishi's place we're headed to is well-known for its live music.
Shiho: I heard she herself sings there sometimes. It'd be great if we could hear her sing today.
Miku: <Hehe, I agree.>
Miku: <You and Ichika had so much to say about this girl that I got really curious about her, so I'd be happy just to see her.>
Miku: <Thanks for bringing me along, Shiho.>
Shiho: Let's see now, we turn here and...
Shiho: Oh. I think that's the place.
Shiho: Alright, let's go. Be careful not to be seen, okay?
Miku: <Got it.>
An: Welcome!
An: Oh, Hinomori!
Shiho: Hello. I'm supposed to be meeting Kohane. Is she here?
An: Yeah! The flyers, right? Wait just a second!
An: Kohane! Hinomori's here!
Kohane: Sorry for having you come all this way, Shiho!
Shiho: Don't mention it. Actually, we're the ones who asked you the favor, so I should be apologizing to you.
An: Hehe. Either way, we don't get many Miya Girls students among our customers. I'm glad you're here.
An: Anyway, you two feel free to use that table over there!
Kohane: Okay! Over here, Shiho!
Shiho & Akito: Oh...
Akito: You're the girl from the School Festival...
Shiho: You're the guy who was scared of the zombie wolf.
Akito: Huh?! Who said I was scared? I was just surprised.
Toya: It was a realistic zombie wolf after all.
Toya: But... I see. So the girl Azusawa was waiting for was you, Hinomori.
Kohane: Yes! Actually Shiho, we all watched your band perform at Shibuya Festa. Your performance was really cool and exciting!
Shiho: Thanks. We were pretty satisfied with our performance that day ourselves.
Shiho: And you were all amazing too. I liked how you sang with so much power.
Kohane: Hehehe, that's good to hear!
An: Though, we all still need to put in the work!
Shiho: Speaking of which, Shiraishi. Weren't you singing out there on the street the other night?
An: Huh?
Shiho: I didn't want to disturb you since you seemed to be concentrating... But you were singing with so much power. Like, enough to make my heart ache.
Kohane: To make your heart ache?
An: Ah... I guess that was when I stayed back after practice. I was pretty in the zone.
An: I'd been wanting to sing with more emotion, so I was practicing that.
Akito: ... I see.
Akito: Well, I get how you sometimes just feel the urge like that. But don't overdo it.
An: Hey, I know that. You worry too much.
An: ... But yeah, thank you!
Shiho: ...?
An: Anyway, our last event was a big success thanks to Kohane, and we need to bring even more energy next time!
Customers: Hey, An's all fired up!
Customers: Now I wanna hear you sing. Can you do just one song?
An: Oh... Sure! I suppose I can spare you one song!
An: On that note, sorry Hinomori! Please give your order to my dad.
Shiho: Got it. Break a leg.
Shiho: (What was with Shiraishi just now...? She seemed a little off.)
Shiho: (Did I say something I shouldn't have?)
Kohane: Oh yeah, Shiho.
Kohane: I left the flyer samples in the back, so I'll go get them now.
Shiho: Got it. Thanks again.
Kohane: No problem! It looks like An's going to sing now, so why don't you listen while you wait?
An: Alright, looks like the mic's on!
Shiho: (Who'd have guessed Shiraishi really would sing for us? Miku's gonna get to hear her after all.)
Shiho: Miku, it looks like Shiraishi's going to sing.
Miku: <So it does. I think I'll listen in.>
An: Okay, here I go!
An: ♪————! ——————!
Miku: (Wow, this girl's just like Shiho said. Her singing is so cool and powerful.)
Miku: (And I think I can see how Ichika had so much to learn from her.)
Miku: (Street music has a totally different kind of power from rock... This feels so new and exciting.)
An: ♪————~~~~!
Customers: Way to go, An!
Customers: One more song!
Shiho: (The customers are so into it. I can tell how much they love her singing... There's a great atmosphere here.)
Shiho: (But...)
Shiho: (It's not quite the same as that time.)
Shiho: (I don't feel the same power that made my heart ache...)
Miku: <She's just like you said, Shiho. She's cool and sings really well.>
Shiho: ...
Miku: <Shiho...?>
Shiho: Oh, uh... It's nothing. I just—
Kohane: Thank you for waiting! Here are the flyer samples!
Shiho: Oh, great. Thanks.
Kohane: I drew up a few different samples based on my discussion with Honami. What do you think?
Shiho: Wow, the overall feel changes a lot with just a tweak to the balance of the text. Which should we go for...?
An: Huff... Okay, it's time to wrap it up!
Customer: Thanks An! You really got some pipes on you!
An: Hehe, that's sweet of you!
An: (But...)
An: (It's not enough... At this level, I'm still so far behind. I need to practice more.)
Miku: Since you want to be someone she can “respect and be proud of”, An, you want her to like and be excited by the way you sing.
Miku: But...
Akito: You're worried about not being able to do that if Kohane keeps improving at her current rate, right...?
An: (I need to practice more, to sing more. Right now, that's...all I can do...)
An: See you later, Hinomori!
Shiho: See you. And Kohane, thanks for all your help.
Kohane: Of course! I'm glad to be of help. Good luck with your solo show!
Shiho: It looks like the flyers will turn out well thanks to Kohane. And on top of that, I got to hear Shiraishi sing.
Shiho: But...
Miku: <Shiho, what's up?>
Shiho: Oh, Miku...
Miku: <You had something on your mind when you were watching Shiraishi before, right?>
Shiho: Yeah. Her singing just now was incredible, but it was pretty different from when I heard it the other night.
Miku: <Different? In what way?>
Shiho: Last time, her singing was so powerful that my heart ached. But I didn't really get that from her today.
Shiho: She was singing so well... So, why do I feel this way...?
